            <entry xml:id="entry_færsūʒyn" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>færsūʒyn</orth><form type="participle"
                            ><orth>færsyǧd</orth></form></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>fælsoʒun</orth><form
                        type="participle"><orth>fælsuǧd</orth></form></form>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>процеживать</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>filter</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>strain</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <re>
                    <form type="lemma"><orth>færsūʒæn</orth></form>
                    <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>цедилка</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>strainer</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>ūrs æxsyr … cæxgærmæ īw ūs færsūʒy</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>белое молоко в кадку одна женщина процеживает</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>one woman filters white milk in a tub</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>73</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Старое сращение преверба %ifær-%i, %ifæl-%i с глаголом <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_sūʒyn"/> | %isoʒun%i означающим самостоятельно
                    ‘сжигать’ (← %i*para-sauč-%i). Странная, по первому впечатлению, семантика
                    (‘сжигать’ || ‘процеживать’) решительно поддерживается другими фактами
                    осетинского языка: <ref type="xr" target="#entry_syǧdæg"/> ‘чистый’, <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_ræsūg"/> | %iræsog%i ‘прозрачный’, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_ræsūǧd"/> ‘красивый’ заключают в себе ту же основу %isuk-%i
                    ‘огонь’, которую мы находим в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_sūʒyn"/> | %isoʒun%i
                    ‘жечь’. В этих словах отражены древние представления, по которым понятия
                    ‘чистоты’, ‘красоты’, ‘прозрачности’ были неотделимы от понятия ‘огня’, не
                    мыслились вне связи с ‘огнем’, как универсальной очищающей стихией. Связь
                    „чистоты“ с „огнем“ прослеживается и в других родственных языках: ср. <mentioned
                        xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>vasūjs-</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (←
                            %i*ava-suč-%i)</note>
                        <gloss><q>очищать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"
                            ><w>vasuta-</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (←
                            %i*ava-suxta-%i)</note>
                        <gloss><q>чистый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*pasūč-, *pasūγt-</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (pswč,
                            pcwγt-)</note>
                        <gloss><q>очищать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>процеживать</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Henning._BBB"/><biblScope>132</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>śōčayāmi</w>
                        <gloss><q>я сжигаю</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>я очищаю</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                            ><w>pavitra-</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">1.</note>
                        <gloss><q>средство воспламенения</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa"><w/><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">2.</note>
                        <gloss><q>средство очищения’ = ‘сито</q></gloss></mentioned>. Неудачно
                    сопоставление %sНаdank%s’a (<bibl><author>Handank</author><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_KPF"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Abt. III, Bd. IV, стр.
                            217</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">Abt. III, Bd. IV, p.
                            217</biblScope></bibl>) с <mentioned xml:lang="zza"><lang/>
                        <w>p%ri%rrôzhin</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="prc"><lang/>
                        <w>paričūn</w>
                        <gloss><q>сито</q></gloss></mentioned>. Ср. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_ræsūǧd"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>29</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                        /><biblScope>72</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">The old contraction of the preverb %ifær-%i, %ifæl-%i with the
                    verb <ref type="xr" target="#entry_sūʒyn"/> | %isoʒun%i which itself means
                    ‘burn’ (← %i*para-sauč-%i). The strange, at first impression, semantics (‘burn’
                    || ‘filter’) is strongly supported by other facts of the Ossetic language: the
                    words <ref type="xr" target="#entry_syǧdæg"/> ‘clean’, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_ræsūg"/> | %iræsog%i ‘transparent’, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_ræsūǧd"/> ‘beautiful’ consist of the same stem %isuk-%i
                    ‘fire’, which is found in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_sūʒyn"/> | %isoʒun%i
                    ‘burn’. These words reflect the ancient ideas, according to which the concepts
                    of ‘purity’, ‘beauty’, ‘transparency’ were inseparable from the concept of
                    ‘fire’, were not thought of outside of connection with ‘fire’ as a universal
                    purifying element. The connection between "purity" and "fire" can be traced in
                    other related languages: cf. <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>vasūjs-</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (←
                            %i*ava-suč-%i)</note>
                        <gloss><q>purify</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"
                            ><w>vasuta-</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (←
                            %i*ava-suxta-%i)</note>
                        <gloss><q>clean</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*pasūč-, *pasūγt-</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (pswč, pcwγt-)</note>
                        <gloss><q>purify</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>filter</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Henning._BBB"/><biblScope>132</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>śōčayāmi</w>
                        <gloss><q>I burn</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>I clean</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                            ><w>pavitra-</w><note
                            type="comment" xml:lang="en">1.</note>
                        <gloss><q>means for ignition</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa"><w/><note
                            type="comment" xml:lang="en">2.</note>
                        <gloss><q>means for cleaning’ = ‘sieve</q></gloss></mentioned>. The
                    %sНаdank%s’s (<bibl><author>Handank</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_KPF"
                            /><biblScope xml:lang="en">Abt. III, Bd. IV, p.
                            217</biblScope></bibl>) comparison to <mentioned xml:lang="zza"><lang/>
                        <w>p%ri%rrôzhin</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="prc"><lang/>
                        <w>paričūn</w>
                        <gloss><q>sieve</q></gloss></mentioned> is unsuccessful. Cf. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_ræsūǧd"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>29</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                        /><biblScope>72</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
